<pageContent>
    <id><![CDATA[OC_SA_R1_D050]]></id>
	<title><![CDATA[<Introtext style="font-family:Helvetica; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold; color:#cc0033; margin:10px -5px 10px 5px; padding:5px 0 5px 5px; background:#e8e8e8; border-bottom:1px solid #333; display:block;">Aligning Your Strategy</Introtext>]]></title>
	<title2><![CDATA[]]></title2>
	<instructions><![CDATA[<welcomeText style=" font-family:Helvetica; font-size:11pt; line-height:18pt; text-align:justify; font-weight:bold; color:#333; display:block; margin:0 10px 10px">As you prepare for your meeting with Dr. Hayes, what action will you plan to take?</welcomeText>]]></instructions>
	<choices>
		<choice>
			<id><![CDATA[1]]></id>
			<isCorrect><![CDATA[NO]]></isCorrect>
			<choiceText><![CDATA[<welcomeText style=" font-family:Helvetica; font-size:12pt; line-height:18pt; text-align:justify; font-weight:normal; color:#333; display:block; margin:0 10px 10px"><b>A</b>. Plan to offer Dr. Hayes information and data that he can use to evaluate his options. Be prepared to help him by providing the features and fair balance of your product.</welcomeText>]]></choiceText>
			<KPIs totalScore="15">
				<KPI marks="5"><![CDATA[Customer Results Score]]></KPI>
				<KPI marks="5"><![CDATA[Sales Progress Score]]></KPI>
				<KPI marks="5"><![CDATA[Trusted Advisor Relationship Score]]></KPI>
			</KPIs>
			<branchTo><![CDATA[OC_SA_R1_D050_A010]]></branchTo>
		</choice>
		<choice>
			<id><![CDATA[2]]></id>
			<isCorrect><![CDATA[NO]]></isCorrect>
			<choiceText><![CDATA[<welcomeText style=" font-family:Helvetica; font-size:12pt; line-height:18pt; text-align:justify; font-weight:normal; color:#333; display:block; margin:0 10px 10px"><b>B</b>. Take time to research the business thoroughly, and identify questions to ask Dr. Hayes in your meeting that will help to accelerate the prescribing cycle. </welcomeText>]]></choiceText>
			<KPIs totalScore="0">
				<KPI marks="5"><![CDATA[Customer Results Score]]></KPI>
				<KPI marks="-10"><![CDATA[Sales Progress Score]]></KPI>
				<KPI marks="5"><![CDATA[Trusted Advisor Relationship Score]]></KPI>
			</KPIs>
			<branchTo><![CDATA[OC_SA_R1_D050_B010]]></branchTo>
		</choice>
		<choice>
			<id><![CDATA[3]]></id>
			<isCorrect><![CDATA[YES]]></isCorrect>
			<choiceText><![CDATA[<welcomeText style=" font-family:Helvetica; font-size:12pt; line-height:18pt; text-align:justify; font-weight:normal; color:#333; display:block; margin:0 10px 10px"><b>C</b>. Prepare to confirm what you have heard from Dr. Bennett with Dr. Hayes, such as Sunnydale Psychiatry’s focus on growth and reputation.  Also, ask Dr. Hayes his vision for patient outcomes.</welcomeText>]]></choiceText>
			<KPIs totalScore="30">
				<KPI marks="10"><![CDATA[Customer Results Score]]></KPI>
				<KPI marks="10"><![CDATA[Sales Progress Score]]></KPI>
				<KPI marks="10"><![CDATA[Trusted Advisor Relationship Score]]></KPI>
			</KPIs>
			<branchTo><![CDATA[OC_SA_R1_D050_C010]]></branchTo>
		</choice>
		<choice>
			<id><![CDATA[4]]></id>
			<isCorrect><![CDATA[NO]]></isCorrect>
			<choiceText><![CDATA[<welcomeText style=" font-family:Helvetica; font-size:12pt; line-height:18pt; text-align:justify; font-weight:normal; color:#333; display:block; margin:0 10px 10px"><b>D</b>. Plan to use the meeting to fully identify and document all of Dr. Hayes’ concerns about prescribing your product, in addition to presenting information. Anticipate his concerns. After all, he is very comfortable with the products he typically prescribes, having used them for years, and naturally he will have reservations.</welcomeText>]]></choiceText>
			<KPIs totalScore="0">
				<KPI marks="5"><![CDATA[Customer Results Score]]></KPI>
				<KPI marks="-10"><![CDATA[Sales Progress Score]]></KPI>
				<KPI marks="5"><![CDATA[Trusted Advisor Relationship Score]]></KPI>
			</KPIs>
			<branchTo><![CDATA[OC_SA_R1_D050_D010]]></branchTo>
		</choice>
	</choices>
    <summary><![CDATA[<welcomeText style=" font-family:Helvetica; font-size:12pt; line-height:18pt; text-align:justify; font-weight:normal; color:#333; display:block; margin:0 10px 10px">Dr. Bennett stated earlier that he and Dr. Hayes are willing to explore other options, so this indicates they are in the evaluating options phase of the prescribing cycle. Because this will be your first conversation with Dr. Hayes, it would be best to confirm the information you have received from Dr. Bennett, and ask Dr. Hayes about the outcomes he hopes to achieve. (Choice C). In this way you are able both to bring value to the customer and to increase their trust in you and your product. Choice A is an okay option, since providing Dr. Hayes criteria to evaluate his options is another appropriate action in this phase of the prescribing cycle, but it doesn’t take into consideration Dr. Hayes’ priorities, and in this instance you want to do both. You should have already researched the practice thoroughly, so Choice B does not move you and your customer forward. Choice D prematurely jumps ahead to deciding to trial instead of providing what is needed for this phase of the prescribing cycle. Choice C is the best choice.</welcomeText>]]></summary>
</pageContent>